        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(auth): support and document --profile-id in models auth login",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `--profile-id` support to `openclaw models auth login` for single-profile auth flows\n- persist the requested profile id when the selected auth method returns exactly one auth profile\n- add focused coverage for the profile-id remapping behavior\n- document the named-profile login flow for Codex OAuth and related auth-order/session-reset usage\n\n## Why\n\nThe docs and installed CLI already point users toward named auth profiles for multi-account setups, especially for `openai-codex`. This PR makes the source repo match that behavior and documents the flow end-to-end.\n\n## Notes\n\n- `--profile-id` intentionally errors when an auth method returns multiple profiles, so we don't silently rename ambiguous results.\n- Docs also fix the `/model <alias-or-id>@<profileId>` placeholder notation for consistency.\n",
